[WNV fever cases are beginning to be detected from many countries in Europe. An increasing number of cases in humans and equine animals have been reported from Europe in recent years. WNV has been present in Europe since the 1950s and is transmitted by mosquitoes.

ECDC started West Nile fever surveillance in 2011 during the mosquito transmission season, in order to inform the blood safety authorities in Europe of areas in the EU and the neighborhood with West Nile cases; according to EU legislation, blood donors from such areas should be deferred or tested [Comment borrowed from Mod.TY]. - Mod.UBA

